        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 8:17AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 817 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
northwestern Pasadena, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pasadena, western Baytown, Deer Park, South Houston, Galena Park,
Jacinto City, South Belt / Ellington, northern Clear Lake,
Cloverleaf, Channelview, Edgebrook Area, Northshore, Ellington Field,
Houston Ship Channel, San Jacinto State Park, and Meadowbrook /
Allendale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
